  "section_name": "Financial Analysis",
  "text": "R&D investment intensity remains elevated at 9.43% of revenue in Q3 2025, with R&D expenses of $8,866,000,000. This represents an increase from Q2 2025 R&D spending of $8,550,000,000, suggesting continued commitment to innovation initiatives including AI capabilities and semiconductor development. The sustained R&D intensity positions Apple to compete in emerging technology categories while maintaining its product differentiation.",
